.TH "gpiod_get_index" 9 "gpiod_get_index" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gpiod_get_index \- obtain a GPIO from a multi-index GPIO function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct gpio_desc *" gpiod_get_index
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *con_id "  ","
.BI "unsigned int idx "  ","
.BI "enum gpiod_flags flags "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
GPIO consumer, can be NULL for system-global GPIOs
.IP "con_id" 12
function within the GPIO consumer
.IP "idx" 12
index of the GPIO to obtain in the consumer
.IP "flags" 12
optional GPIO initialization flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This variant of \fBgpiod_get\fP allows to access GPIOs other than the first
defined one for functions that define several GPIOs.

Return a valid GPIO descriptor, -ENOENT if no GPIO has been assigned to the
requested function and/or index, or another \fBIS_ERR\fP code if an error
occurred while trying to acquire the GPIO.
